<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3521"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3521-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3521">Improve Revision System for Posted Ideas&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5804-4049">Bryan Rosander</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The current revision system allows several opportunities for fraud and abuse.  It is also inconsistent and encourages people to post duplicates for minor improvements.<br/><br/>I propose that:<br/>The title, description, and Why is This Idea Important sections should be able to be revised.<br/>A history of changes should be viewable for each post.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3521" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3521', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2255&topicID=3521')">Comments (2)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3521"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2255">Uncategorized</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=site improvement">site improvement</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=revision">revision</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3521"></div>
