<div id="Idea_3518"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3518-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3518">Lobbying&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6502-4049">jellis</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Outlaw nontransparent lobbying. The intent here is not to ofend anyone. However, as long as the the big moneyed, special interests have such intimate access to our elected officials, which is beyond the means of most "normal" citizens there is, in my opinion to much influence being "paid for". I hope this gets my point across better.  </div>
