<div id="Idea_3517"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3517-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3517">A bonus for employees in a department of government that comes in under budget.&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4612-4049">azaleahs</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Not for the boss but for the employees.<br/><br/>set the amount of the bonus as a percentage of the amount under budget.<br/><br/>I had a manager who didn't order supplies for an entire quarter and they gave her a promotion for it. The next manager had to order all those supplies and got in trouble  for going over budget. That kind of foolery shouldn't be allowed.</div>
