<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3504"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3504-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3504">Federal Subsidy of Public Transportation. Free Bus Passes for ALL.&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5672-4049">Greg Vanderlaan</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Reducing the ticket price of a city bus, light rail and subway to zero would increase ridership and reduce the number of cars on the road. Fewer cars would mean fewer traffic jams for those that still choose to drive. A dramatic increase in the quality of life for commuters. Fewer cars would reduce oil imports... reduce pollution... increase miles per gallon (traffic jams cause terrible mpg). With ridership increasing, the transit system could increase the quantity of buses and schedule more routes and more times. That would make public transportation practical for more commuters. Create jobs for bus drivers and mechanics. <br/><br/>more info: http://gregvanderlaan.com</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3504" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3504', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2255&topicID=3504')">Comments (4)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3504"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2255">Uncategorized</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=subsidize">subsidize</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=bus">bus</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=light rail">light rail</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=subway">subway</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=public transportation">public transportation</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=oil">oil</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=gas">gas</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=cars">cars</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=traffic">traffic</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3504"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_3487">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_3487">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3487', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2255&topicID=3487&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 4 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 3</div><div>Votes Against : 4</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3487'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_3487" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 4 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 3</div><div>Votes Against : 4</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_3487'))">-1</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_3487', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2255&topicID=3487&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3487"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3487-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3487">People Oriented Services!&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6422-4049">alpha371</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">From Education to the logistics of Life, P.O.S. is a way to get exactly what you need, when and where you want it. With technologies as they stand today, it is possible to 1) accommodate most customers’ needs, 2) streamline the costs of living and waste, and 3) improve education and expedite qualified individuals to the job of their choosing. Imagine being able to determine your own futures and your children have career ambitions before graduating school; the quality of one's life has largely been based on a number of factors like money, transportation, and living accommodations. I find that a strong community can counteract an individual's shortcomings and focus on a growth conducive for all.<br/><br/>It does work! Unfortunately, I can not go into too much detail, because it is a secret to my success. I have begun implementing many of these concepts into my business. They are not ready for national service yet and require more research and development. <br/><br/>Finally, the places I do see P.O.S. having a positive impact on day to day operations: <br/>-Business<br/>-Education<br/>-Cost of living<br/>-Transportation<br/>-Economics<br/>-Real Estate <br/>-National Service <br/>-Technology<br/>-Entertainment<br/>-Government<br/>- and Health Care<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3487" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3487', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2255&topicID=3487')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3487"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2255">Uncategorized</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=yea">yea</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3487"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</table>

